metadata.title: Waves of Ink: Pacific Northwest Maritime Trade, 1851–61
metadata.author: Sean Fraga
metadata.description:
This project interprets the first U.S. Customs ledger for the Puget Sound Customs District, covering the first decade of initial American settlement of the Puget Sound basin. 

More information, and links to the complete transcription, can be found at the project webpage: seanfraga.com/waves of ink.

This Palladio dataset has been adapted and simplified from the full ledger transcription in the following ways.

- Voyages without full date information (YYYY-MM-DD) have been removed. Dates for some outbound voyages have been interpolated from dates for corresponding inbound voyages.

- Some country- or region-level places have been linked to specific geographic coordinates to major ports already in the shipping records, as follows:
	Australia —> Melbourne
	New South Wales —> Melbourne
	Bellingham Bay —> Whatcom
	China —> Hong Kong
	England —> London
	Hawaiian Islands —> Honolulu
	Peru —> Callao
	Vancouver’s Island —> Victoria

- Other regional place names have not been assigned specific geographic coordinates (such as "From Sea," or "Ports in South Pacific").

- This table includes information about vessel masters and vessel cargo for each voyage, but this data isn't consistently formatted
